    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Is the scan painful?",
        "answer": "No. You may feel a cool contrast injection, but no cutting or needles inside the body.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How soon can I eat after contrast MRI?",
        "answer": "Right away—unless your doctor has ordered additional fasting tests.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I drive home after sedation?",
        "answer": "No. Bring a companion if you took a sedative.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "When will reports be ready?",
        "answer": "By 6 p.m. next working day; urgent cases within 2 hours.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Does insurance cover MRI abdomen pelvis?",
        "answer": "Most policies cover medically necessary scans. Our front desk will pre-authorise your claim instantly.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What is the cost of an abdomen and pelvis MRI scan?",
        "answer": "  The **cost of an abdomen and pelvis MRI scan** can vary depending on several factors, including the complexity of the scan and whether contrast material is used. For specific pricing information for your **Abdomen and Pelvis MRI Scan** at Cadabams Diagnostics, please contact us directly or visit our pricing page "
      }
